# Stack Auth — architecture & adapters (core)

This project uses Stack Auth (self-hosted) via an adapter pattern.
Docs: https://docs.stack-auth.com

## Architecture

```
src/stack/client.ts                      — getStackClientApp()
src/stack/server.ts                      — getStackServerApp()
src/lib/auth/providers/stack/*-adapter.* — Stack integration layer
src/app/handler/[...stack]/page.tsx      — <StackHandler />
src/app/loading.tsx                      — global loading boundary (Stack best practice)
```

## Usage rules

### Forbidden (to avoid breakage)

- ❌ **Do not create** `new StackClientApp(...)` / `new StackServerApp(...)` in app code  
  Use `getStackClientApp()` / `getStackServerApp()`.
- ❌ **Do not implement auth/session in API routes via Stack SDK directly** — only via our adapters/helpers.

### Allowed (and required)

- ✅ **UI layer** (`src/app/**`, `src/features/auth/**`): use Stack components/hooks per docs  
  (`useUser`, `useStackApp`, `<OAuthButtonGroup />`, `<SignIn />`, etc.)
- ✅ **Server/API layer**: use our adapters/helpers:
  - client: `getAuthClientAdapter()` from `src/lib/auth/providers/client-factory.tsx`
  - server: `getAuthAdapter()` from `src/lib/auth/providers/factory.ts`

## Required wrappers (UI)

**CRITICAL:** `StackProvider` + `StackTheme` must exist in the tree (we add them in `client-adapter.tsx`).  
shadcn `TooltipProvider` must also exist (we add it in `providers.tsx`) or Stack tooltips will crash.

❌ **Do not remove** `StackTheme` from the provider — built-in Stack components will break.
